          h2 Open API Layer for a Legacy Core 
          a(href="").button.btn__bookacall Download Full PDF
        .head__right 
          img(src='assets/images/study-illus1.png' alt='Case Study Illustration')
      .body
        h3 Whats Inside (highlights):
        .item__list
          .item__list-content
            img(src="assets/images/mingcute_check-fill.svg" alt="")
            span Built a UNI-RAIL middleware layer that exposes stable, versioned REST endpoints (OpenAPI) over a legacy/mainframe core that only provided CSV and batch interfaces; added HMAC-signed webhooks(instruction.created, instruction.settled, rfi.*).
          .item__list-content
            img(src="assets/images/mingcute_check-fill.svg" alt="")
            span Adapter pattern: host adapters (MQ/DB2/screen automation as last resort), batch-to-event converter, CSV/flat-file parsers, ISO-20022-inspired canonical objects for accounts, instructions, and reconciliation.
          .item__list-content
            img(src="assets/images/mingcute_check-fill.svg" alt="")
            span Governance portal with policy-as-code (OPA), RBAC, dual-control approvals, audit trails, and observability(request IDs, traces, error budgets).
          .item__list-content
            img(src="assets/images/mingcute_check-fill.svg" alt="")
            span SLOs aligned to your master schedules: 99.9% availability, ≤100 ms median / ≤500 ms P99 on core paths; acceptance via KPI reviews.
        br
        br
        h3 Why the references include “IFS” and “FIS”:
        .item__list
          .item__list-content
            img(src="assets/images/mingcute_check-fill.svg" alt="")
            span The client’s stack did not expose modern external REST APIs. As market context, enterprise vendors like FISprovide core platforms (Profile/IBS) and API gateways (Code Connect) for modernization; meanwhile IFS Cloudshows an OpenAPI-first approach in enterprise software (useful for API governance patterns).
